x4freetext: 4.5 MV Van de Graaff Accelerator
The monoenergetic neutrons were produced
through the 2H(d,n)3He reaction with a deuterium gas
target. The length of the target gas cell is 2.0 cm,
and separated from the vacuum tube with a molybdenum
foil of 5.0 um in thickness. A gold foil of 0.2 mm
in thickness was used as the beam dump at the
downstream side of the gas cell. The deuterium gas
pressure in the gas cell was 2.9 to 3.1 atm, and the
intensity of the deuteron beam was about 3.0 uA.
The gridded ionization chamber (GIC) with
symmetric double sections acted as the alpha particle
detector. The distances from the cathode to grid,
grid to anode and anode to shield were 61, 15 and 9
mm, respectively. The working gas in the GIC was a
mixture of Kr+CO2(2.82%).
The BF3 long counter worked as the neutron flux
monitor for normalization of background subtraction
and for absolute neutron flux calibration. The
external diameter of this proportional counter is 38
mm, and the active length is about 25 cm.
The material of the 40Ca sample
is natural CaF2 (purity 98.5%). The circular film
samples were prepared on tantalum backings by using
the vacuum evaporation method. A stack of two CaF2
samples were installed at the center of the GIC, the
sample thickness of forward and backward were 364.5
and 339.8 ug/cm2, the sample diameter of forward and
backward were 4.35 and 4.20 cm. The tantalum backing
layers with 0.1 mm thick were faced with each other.
With back-to-back samples, alpha particles emitted to
both forward (0 to 90 degree) and backward (90 to 180
degree) angles with respect to the beam axis can be
detected simultaneously.
A separate run was performed with 238U on 0.1 mm thick
Ta for neutron flux calibration.
The total uncertainty.
Fission counts 2.5%
BF3 counts normalization 1.5%
Number of the 40Ca nucleus 1.0%
Number of the 238U nucleus 1.3%
238U(n,f) cross sections 1.0%
Compiled by WANG Jimin (CNDC).
Alpha counting statistics (3%-7%)
Data were obtained from TABLES 5-10 of
Appendix A. of Eur.Phys.J.A,51,12,2015.
